casebody.data:
Timothy Nelson BUTLER, Appellant,
v.
The STATE of Florida, Appellee. No. 3D19-189 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed April 3, 2019 Timothy Nelson Butler, in proper person. Ashley Moody, Attorney General, for appellee. Before FERNANDEZ, LOGUE, and MILLER, JJ. PER CURIAM.

Affirmed. See Mendenhall v. State , 48 So.3d 740 , 742 (Fla. 2010) (holding that under section 775.087, Florida Statutes, "the trial court has discretion ... to impose a mandatory minimum ... even if that mandatory minimum exceeds the statutory maximum.").
